Description: Fragment of double handle at neck join from a Koan pottery transport amphora. Clay fine light brown; cream slip. Rectangular stamp with Greek inscription.
Curator's comments: Petrie diary, 1884-1885 (EES Archive XVII 47), p. 101a, 54? The pencil mark is not fully consistent consistent with Naukratis as the provenance. Name, Dionysios. Pencil '39'.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0186)
